Here is the updated function:

```javascript
function doesItContainTableOrColumns(text) {
  // Split the text into lines
  const lines = text.split('\n');
  // Check if any line contains multiple words separated by spaces
  const hasColumns = lines.some(line => line.trim().split(/\s+/).length > 1);
  // Check if there are multiple lines with the same number of columns
  const hasRows = lines.filter(line => line.trim().split(/\s+/).length > 1).length > 1;
  // If there are both rows and columns, it's likely to be a table
  if (hasRows && hasColumns) {
    return "TABLE";
  }
  // If there are only columns without multiple rows, it's columns
  else if (hasColumns) {
    return "COLUMNS";
  }
  // If there are multiple rows without columns, it's also a table
  else if (hasRows) {
    return "TABLE";
  }
  // If none of the above conditions are met, return "NORMAL"
  else {
    return "NORMAL";
  }
}
```

With this update, the function checks for both the presence of columns and rows based on the structure of the text. If there are multiple rows with columns, it will be classified as a "TABLE". If there are only columns without multiple rows, it will be classified as "COLUMNS". If there are multiple rows without columns, it will also be classified as a "TABLE". If none of the above conditions are met, it will be classified as "NORMAL".

